{"name": "stl-compressor", "metadata": {"name": "stl-compressor", "version": "2.6", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/fan-ziqi/stl_compressor", "license": "Apache License 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["open3d"], "summary": "STL Compressor", "upload_time": 1733195913}, "documentation": ["# STL Compressor\n\nSTL Compressor is a tool designed to compress STL files efficiently. Users can conveniently compress multiple STL files in batches, reducing their file sizes without compromising on quality.\n\n## Usage\n\nInstall with pip\n\n```bash\npip install stl_compressor\nstl_compressor\n```\n\nYou can also download the Windows exe file [here](https://github.com/fan-ziqi/stl_compressor/releases)\n\n## Packaging\n\nTo package the application as a standalone exe file for windows, use PyInstaller:\n\n```bash\npyinstaller --onefile --windowed stl_compressor/stl_compressor_ui.py\n```\n\n## Upload to Pypi\n\n```bash\npython setup.py check\npython setup.py sdist bdist_wheel\ntwine upload dist/*\n```\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "stl_compressor", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.target_number_of_triangles", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.current_directory", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.input_directory", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.output_directory", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.mesh", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.simplified_mesh", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stl_compressor.stl_compressor_test.output_file_